All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Map<K,V>
public final class SortedArrayBackedMap<K,V>
extends AbstractArrayBackedMap<K,V>

Sorted implementation of AbstractArrayBackedMap. An instance may be created with or without a Comparator. No specified comparator indicates that the natural ordering of elements should be used. You'll see ClassCastExceptions if the keys are not mutually comparable, similarly to TreeMap.

Author:
Joe Kearney

getIndexForNewEntry

protected int getIndexForNewEntry(K key,
                                  V value)
Description copied from class: AbstractArrayBackedMap
Gets the index for insertion of a new key-value pair, where the key is not currently in the map. The index may depend on the key and/or the value. The returned value must be in the range [0, size()]. If it is equal to size of the map prior to this insertion, then the new entry will be placed at the tail of the array.

Specified by:
getIndexForNewEntry in class AbstractArrayBackedMap<K,V>
Parameters:
key - the new key
value - the new value
Returns:
index at which to insert the new key-value pair
